<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-05-12T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-05-12T09:00:00-05:00" n="413" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d413">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/5646: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany (<persName corresp="#p_SFM1" type="from">Sackett</persName>) to the
                                        <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-05-12T15:00:00+01:00">May
                                        12, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received May 12—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>95. Your 50, May 11, 6 p.m. Have seen Ministerial Director <persName corresp="#p_RK1">Ritter</persName>. Based on promising outlook
                                of negotiations in Washington as today reported by German
                                Ambassador, I have reason to believe favorable solution can be
                                expected here. In spite of holidays matter will be submitted to
                                Cabinet for decision after Reichstag adjournment which is expected
                                today, and I hope to report definitely early next week.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SFM1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sackett</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>